<subSubSection id="C3776556ED4B382FFCEFFB8DFBEBFB9C" box="[810,1070,1091,1117]" pageId="538" pageNumber="539" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED4B382FFCEFFB8DFBEBFB9C" blockId="538.[810,1070,1091,1117]" box="[810,1070,1091,1117]" pageId="538" pageNumber="539">
<heading id="D09A81B1ED4B382FFCEFFB8DFBEBFB9C" bold="true" box="[810,1070,1091,1117]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="538" pageNumber="539" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4B382FFCEFFB8DFBEBFB9C" bold="true" box="[810,1070,1091,1117]" pageId="538" pageNumber="539">
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED4B382FFCEFFB8DFC7CFB9C" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[810,953,1091,1117]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Ammonixys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="538" pageNumber="539" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4B382FFCEFFB8DFC7CFB9C" bold="true" box="[810,953,1091,1117]" italics="true" pageId="538" pageNumber="539">Ammonixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED4B382FFC05FB8DFBEBFB9C" box="[960,1070,1091,1117]" pageId="538" pageNumber="539" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED4B382FFCEFFB49FB5DF8E6" pageId="538" pageNumber="539" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED4B382FFCEFFB49FB5DF8E6" blockId="538.[810,1452,1159,2070]" pageId="538" pageNumber="539">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4B382FFCEFFB49FC58FB60" bold="true" box="[810,925,1159,1185]" pageId="538" pageNumber="539">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Body globular with swollen, almost spherical, fourthpedigerous somite. Freeurosome 5-segmented. Caudalsetae obscure. Rostrum well-developed.Antennule small, 6-segmented. Antenna 4-segmented withsmall terminal claw. Mandible with 4 teeth on coxal gnathobase; exopod fused with basis, represented by 2 setae; endopod 2-segmented with 1 and 4 setae on first and second segments, respectively. Maxillulewith 6 setaeon arthrite, 1 each on coxal epipodite and basis, 4 on exopod and 3 on endopod; coxal endite absent. Maxilla 4-segmented; syncoxa with 2 endites; basis with claw plus 1 seta; endopod 2-segmented. Maxilliped as unsegmented lobe bearing 4 setae. Legs 1–3 with 3-segmented rami. Leg 4 with 3-segmented exopod and 2-segmented endopod. Innercoxalsetaabsentinlegs 1–4. Leg 1 lacking inner distal element on basis. First and second exopodal segments of legs 1–4 lacking inner seta. First and second endopodal segments of legs 1–3 lacking inner seta. Leg 5 represented by lobe and tapering, sclerotized process located ventrodistally on somite.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED4B382FFC9AF8FEFBA9F8AD" pageId="538" pageNumber="539" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED4B382FFC9AF8FEFBA9F8AD" blockId="538.[810,1452,1159,2070]" pageId="538" pageNumber="539">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4B382FFC9AF8FEFC3CF888" bold="true" box="[863,1017,1839,1866]" pageId="538" pageNumber="539">
<typeStatus id="54D6887FED4B382FFC9AF8FEFC3CF888" box="[863,1017,1839,1866]" pageId="538" pageNumber="539">Typespecies</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED4B382FFBCBF8FEFADEF88B" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[1038,1307,1840,1866]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Ammonixys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="538" pageNumber="539" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadridens" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4B382FFBCBF8FEFADEF88B" box="[1038,1307,1840,1866]" italics="true" pageId="538" pageNumber="539">Ammonixysquadridens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4B382FFAEDF8FEFC9EF8AD" bold="true" pageId="538" pageNumber="539">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED4B382FFAEDF8FEFC9EF8AD" pageId="538" pageNumber="539" rank="species">gen. etsp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by original designation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED4B382FFC9AF8BAFBFEF813" pageId="538" pageNumber="539" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED4B382FFC9AF8BAFBFEF813" blockId="538.[810,1452,1159,2070]" pageId="538" pageNumber="539">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4B382FFC9AF8BAFC25F84F" bold="true" box="[863,992,1908,1934]" pageId="538" pageNumber="539">Etymology</emphasis>
. The name is derived from the Greek 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4B382FFCEFF858FCB9F86E" box="[810,892,1942,1967]" italics="true" pageId="538" pageNumber="539">ammon</emphasis>
(=African) and 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4B382FFBF1F858FBA5F86E" box="[1076,1120,1942,1967]" italics="true" pageId="538" pageNumber="539">ixys</emphasis>
, referring to the discovery of the new genus in Africa.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED4B3829FC9AF814FB47F9F8" lastPageId="540" lastPageNumber="541" pageId="538" pageNumber="539" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED4B3829FC9AF814FB47F9F8" blockId="538.[810,1452,1159,2070]" lastBlockId="540.[810,1452,1499,1594]" lastPageId="540" lastPageNumber="541" pageId="538" pageNumber="539">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4B382FFC9AF814FC09F835" bold="true" box="[863,972,2010,2036]" pageId="538" pageNumber="539">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED4B382FFC1CF814FB9FF835" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[985,1114,2010,2036]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Ammonixys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="538" pageNumber="539" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4B382FFC1CF814FB9FF835" box="[985,1114,2010,2036]" italics="true" pageId="538" pageNumber="539">Ammonixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4B382FFBA4F814FB0CF835" bold="true" box="[1121,1225,2010,2036]" pageId="538" pageNumber="539">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED4B382FFBA4F814FB0CF835" box="[1121,1225,2010,2036]" pageId="538" pageNumber="539" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED4B382FFA83F814FA69F832" authorityName="Kerschner" authorityYear="1879" box="[1350,1452,2010,2035]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doroixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="538" pageNumber="539" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4B382FFA83F814FA69F832" box="[1350,1452,2010,2035]" italics="true" pageId="538" pageNumber="539">Doroixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the absence of the inner seta on the proximal endopodal segment(s) of legs 2–4, but the new genus exhibits a striking derived feature separating it from 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED4D3829FDB7FA30FD1DF9D6" authorityName="Kerschner" authorityYear="1879" box="[626,728,1534,1559]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doroixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="540" pageNumber="541" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4D3829FDB7FA30FD1DF9D6" box="[626,728,1534,1559]" italics="true" pageId="540" pageNumber="541">Doroixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and other genera, namely, the loss of a distinct mandibular exopod. The exopod is respresented only by a pair of setae originating on the surface of the fused basis plus exopod. The setation of leg 1 is also distinctive because the first and second exopodal and endopodal segments of leg 1 all lack an inner seta, and the basis of leg 1 is unarmed. This setation of leg 1 differs from that expressed by the four new genera described above, 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4D3829FD44F8C0FCCCF8E9" box="[641,777,1806,1832]" italics="true" pageId="540" pageNumber="541">Prodoroixys</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4D3829FF4DF8FEFF32F88B" bold="true" box="[136,247,1840,1866]" pageId="540" pageNumber="541">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED4D3829FF4DF8FEFF32F88B" box="[136,247,1840,1866]" pageId="540" pageNumber="541" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4D3829FECEF8FEFEA8F888" box="[267,365,1840,1865]" italics="true" pageId="540" pageNumber="541">Notoixys</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4D3829FEBFF8FEFE35F88B" bold="true" box="[378,496,1840,1866]" pageId="540" pageNumber="541">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED4D3829FEBFF8FEFE2FF88B" box="[378,490,1840,1866]" pageId="540" pageNumber="541" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
,
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED4D3829FE39F8FEFD97F888" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[508,594,1840,1865]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Borixys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="540" pageNumber="541" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4D3829FE39F8FEFD97F888" box="[508,594,1840,1865]" italics="true" pageId="540" pageNumber="541">Borixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4D3829FD9AF8FEFD0BF88B" bold="true" box="[607,718,1840,1866]" pageId="540" pageNumber="541">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED4D3829FD9AF8FEFD0BF88B" box="[607,718,1840,1866]" pageId="540" pageNumber="541" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED4D3829FF4DF89CFF20F8AD" authority="Although" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[136,229,1874,1900]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Cystixys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="540" pageNumber="541" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4D3829FF4DF89CFF20F8AD" box="[136,229,1874,1900]" italics="true" pageId="540" pageNumber="541">Cystixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4D3829FF2BF89CFE9CF8AD" bold="true" box="[238,345,1874,1900]" pageId="540" pageNumber="541">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED4D3829FF2BF89CFE9CF8AD" box="[238,345,1874,1900]" pageId="540" pageNumber="541" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
Although the loss of inner setae from the exopod of leg 1 occurs in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED4D3829FE20F8BAFD8FF84F" authorityName="Ooishi" authorityYear="2006" box="[485,586,1908,1934]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Loboixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="540" pageNumber="541" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4D3829FE20F8BAFD8FF84F" box="[485,586,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="540" pageNumber="541">Loboixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the latter genus usually retains the inner setae on the endopod of leg 1. Unlike in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED4D3829FF3DF876FEBCF813" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[248,377,1976,2002]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Ammonixys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="540" pageNumber="541" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4D3829FF3DF876FEBCF813" box="[248,377,1976,2002]" italics="true" pageId="540" pageNumber="541">Ammonixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4D3829FE45F876FE2DF813" bold="true" box="[384,488,1976,2002]" pageId="540" pageNumber="541">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED4D3829FE45F876FE2DF813" box="[384,488,1976,2002]" pageId="540" pageNumber="541" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, the seven known species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED4D3829FF6DF814FEC8F835" authorityName="Ooishi" authorityYear="2006" box="[168,269,2010,2036]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Loboixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="540" pageNumber="541" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4D3829FF6DF814FEC8F835" box="[168,269,2010,2036]" italics="true" pageId="540" pageNumber="541">Loboixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
each have a 3-segmented antenna and carry 6 setae on the maxilliped. This constitutes an additional significant difference between 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED4D3829FB4FFA15FB2AFA34" authorityName="Ooishi" authorityYear="2006" box="[1162,1263,1499,1525]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Loboixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="540" pageNumber="541" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4D3829FB4FFA15FB2AFA34" box="[1162,1263,1499,1525]" italics="true" pageId="540" pageNumber="541">Loboixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED4D3829FAEFFA12FA6EFA37" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[1322,1451,1500,1526]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Ammonixys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="540" pageNumber="541" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4D3829FAEFFA12FA6EFA37" box="[1322,1451,1500,1526]" italics="true" pageId="540" pageNumber="541">Ammonixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFED4D3829FCEFFA30FC50F9D9" bold="true" box="[810,917,1534,1560]" pageId="540" pageNumber="541">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED4D3829FCEFFA30FC50F9D9" box="[810,917,1534,1560]" pageId="540" pageNumber="541" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, which has a 4-segmented antenna and carries only 4 setae on the maxilliped.
</paragraph>
